<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-11-29T14:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-11-29T14:30:00-05:00" n="898" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d898">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/11–2950: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Joint Chiefs of Staff to the Commander in Chief, Far
                            East</hi> (<hi rend="italic">MacArthur</hi>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">flash</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-11-29T14:30:00-05:00">29 November
                                1950—2:30 p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>JCS 97592. We approve your plan in last paragraph of your C 69953<note n="1" xml:id="d898fn1">Received at 4:46 a. m. on November 28, <ref target="#pg_1237">p. 1237</ref>.</note> and any directive in
                        conflict therewith is deferred. Strategic and tactical considerations are
                        now paramount. What are your plans regarding the coordination of operations
                        of the Eighth Army and X Corps and the positioning of X Corps the units of
                        which appear to us to be exposed?</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>